<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4495] Candidates from already resolved fragments get ignored if no new hosts are available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4495</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.felix.resolver.Candidates.populateResource(ResolveContext, Resource) gets called for fragments even if they are already resolved so that we can attach them to more hosts as needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is that this method will throw a ResolutionException if the fragment cannot attach to any new hosts during the current resolve process.  This has the effect of removing any candidate capabilities provided by already resolved fragments.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
